Pick screen color and print it.

Usage: pikcolior [OPTIONS]

Options:
  -c, --copy
          Copy to the clipboard

  -f, --format <FORMAT>
          Print format, can be repeated to print multiple formats separated by newlines
          
          [default: hex]

          Possible values:
          - hex:   #RRGGBB
          - hex16: #RRRRGGGGBBBB
          - float: R.float G.float B.float

      --case <CASE>
          "u": Uppercase/#RRGGBB or "l": lowercase/#rrggbb
          
          [default: u]

  -r, --round <ROUND>
          Rounding strategy when converting from the detected floating-point numbers, default: nearest
          
          [default: n]

          Possible values:
          - n: Round to nearest
          - u: Round up
          - d: Round down

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')

  -V, --version
          Print version
